  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - 61. The development hereby approved shall achieve a minimum of a 35% reduction in CO2 emissions below the maximum threshold set in Building Regulations Part L 2013. \n(a)\tPrior to the first occupation of any Plot, a timetable for the following shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority:\n\"\tTimings for connection to the District Heat Network (as evidenced through relevant documentation);\n\"\tSubmission of as-built evidence (e.g. photographs, copies of installation contracts and as-built worksheets prepared under SAP or the National Calculation Method)\nAny updates to the approved timetable that are subsequently required must also be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, as a submission pursuant to this condition.\n(b)\tAs-built evidence (e.g. photographs, copies of installation contracts and as-built worksheets prepared under SAP or the National Calculation Method) confirming that the development has achieved at least 35% reduction in CO2 emissions below the maximum threshold set out in Building Regulations Part L 2013, or as otherwise set out in the approved Energy Strategy for that Plot, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority in accordance with the timetable (or approved update) approved under part (a) of this condition and no later than 6 months following the identified connection date to the District Heat Network.\nReason: In the interests of sustainable development in accordance with Council policies IS2 and DMS3.\"\n"
  ],
  "decision_date": "16/05/2022",
  "last_updated_by": "Planning Portal ingest",
  "description": "Application under Section 96A of the Town and Country Planning Act for a 'non-material amendment' to Condition 61 (CO2 emissions reductions: to phase the submission requirements to allow for connection to the District Heat Network) of planning permission dated 18th December 2020 reference 2019/2250: \"Application under Section 73 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 for variations to Conditions 9 (Parameter Plans), 10 (GEA Floorspace Limits), 34 (BREEAM) and 52 (Wind Mitigation) of part outline and part detail planning permission 2017/6762 dated 28th March 2019 for \"Minor Material Amendment pursuant to Conditions 1 (time limit), 2 (time limit for\nreserved matters), 9 (parameter plans), 11 (Maximum Floorspaces), 15 (distribution and internal configuration of residential units for each plot), 32 (construction sequence and delivery plan) and 41 (land and groundwater contamination) of part outline and part detailed planning permission 2016/2424, dated 23rd January 2017 for \"Minor Material Amendment pursuant to Conditions 3 (reserved matters), 9 (parameter plans), 10 (GEA floorspace limits), 13 (residential unit limit), 18\n(car parking space limit), 32 (B8 use restriction) and 41 (land and groundwater contamination) of part outline and part detailed planning permission 2011/2462, dated 30/03/12 for demolition of all existing buildings and construction of a mixed use redevelopment comprising 7 building plots with buildings up to 23 storeys high to provide residential units; commercial and community floorspace; associated basement parking and part of the 'Nine Elms Linear Park'. All matters reserved apart\nfrom the appearance and scale of Blocks B1, D1 & G and two new access points from Nine Elms Lane.\" An addendum to the Environmental Statement has been submitted under The Town and Country Planning (Environmental Impact Assessment) Regulations 2017 (as amended).\"",
